The paper deals with a wireless communication network and proposes a game-theoretic solution to reduce communication time. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions coalition games and coalition formation games, which are topics in Game Theory (cs.GT). The paper also deals with a decentralized and partially connected network, which could fall under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a distributed algorithm, which could fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
